Weddings
| WEDDINGS/CELEBRATIONS 
Stephanie Zimand and Jon Plexico

OCT. 9, 2005



Continue reading the main story
Share This Page

Continue reading the main story









Stephanie Folks Zimand, a daughter of Ingeborg R. Zimand and Harvey Folks Zimand of New York, was married yesterday to Jon Mabrey Plexico, the son of Virginia Penn Plexico of Chatham, Mass., and the late Jon Lindsey Plexico. The Rev. Dr. William Rolland, a Presbyterian minister, officiated at the Stonepine Estate, a resort in Carmel Valley, Calif.The bride, 37, is studying for a master's degree in psychology at Dominican University in San Rafael, Calif. She graduated from Rollins College.The bridegroom, 36, was until last month a managing director at Merriman Curhan Ford, a San Francisco investment bank. He graduated from Colgate.Ms. Zimand and Mr. Plexico met at a Halloween party in San Francisco in 2001, but a case of mistaken identity nearly ended their courtship before it began.

Advertisement

Continue reading the main story

Mr. Plexico wrote down the phone numbers of two women named Stephanie. He wanted to be friends with one and hoped to date the other, Ms. Zimand. Continue reading the main story







Advertisement

Continue reading the main story





A few days later he called what he thought was Ms. Zimand's number to ask her to dinner. At the restaurant he was surprised to find the other Stephanie.
