"I thought to myself, 'Well, there's no backing out now, I'm not going to tell her she was the wrong girl,"' Mr. Plexico recalled. So he and his surprise date ordered their meal and enjoyed a pleasant conversation."I was so embarrassed that I never called the right Stephanie," he said. Three years later, Mr. Plexico saw Ms. Zimand again, at a cocktail party."I was able to set the record straight," he said.That night, Ms. Zimand told him that the other Stephanie, a friend of hers, had described him as having had a "deer in the headlights" look when he walked through the restaurant door and said she knew immediately that he had asked out the wrong woman. Ms. Zimand told him she had held onto his business card for a year and a half, wondering why he didn't call.Time and love healed all, and the other Stephanie was a guest at the wedding. Continue reading the main story






